3.584 .358(Lack of Implementation)J
23 68 :M
f0_10 sf
-.003(In the absence of a full-time staff researching language issues for C++, the committee has relied heavily on)A
23 80 :M
-.022(implementors to raise issues discovered while adding new feature support to their compilers.  There has been no such)A
23 92 :M
-.014(feedback from implementors about template template parameters.  It would be very risky to assume that there are no)A
23 104 :M
-.013(serious undiscovered problems, given that there are no implementations.)A
23 128 :M
-.002(It is far too late to make use of any implementor feedback on template template parameters now.)A
23 164 :M
f1_10 sf
2.942 .294(Trivial Workaround)J
23 188 :M
f0_10 sf
-.013(When template template parameters were first proposed, member templates did not exist.  But as has been pointed out,)A
23 200 :M
.051 .005(most of the utility of template template parameters can be had by wrapping the template in a class and passing the class)J
23 212 :M
-.011(instead of the template.  In the past we have rejected many proposed extensions on the grounds that there was a simple)A
23 224 :M
-.028(\(if less elegant\) alternative, so the language feature was not really necessary.)A
23 248 :M
.066 .007(Given that current implementations do not support template template parameters, one must assume that anyone who)J
23 260 :M
-.005(needs the facility must be using the workaround.  Yet we have heard no complaints about how the workaround is less)A
23 272 :M
-.02(effective than template template parameters themselves would be.  So one must conclude that either the workaround is)A
23 284 :M
-.037(acceptable, or hardly anyone is using the workaround - so hardly anyone would use template template parameters if they)A
23 296 :M
-.133(were supported.)A
23 332 :M
f1_10 sf
.933(Conclusions)A
23 356 :M
f0_10 sf
-.041(Template template parameters are ill-specified, there is no implementation experience, and there is a trivial workaround)A
23 368 :M
.145 .015(to their absence.  Given that there is no time to finish their specification, no time to get implementation experience, and)J
23 380 :M
.084 .008(leaving them out does not appear to cause any problems, the only safe route is to remove them from the language.)J
